---
/*
  /honest — what isn't true yet.

  The page that beats every reviewer-style critique by getting there
  first. Three honest gaps named in plain language: only one signer
  so far, only one corridor, no production users. For each gap: what
  is true now, what would change it, what an interested reader could
  do about it.

  Doctrine: a funder, AI lab, or skeptical reviewer should leave this
  page understanding (a) we know what isn't true, (b) we know what
  would make it true, (c) it's an invitation, not a defence. Operator
  voice, not promoter voice.
*/

import Page from "../layouts/Page.astro";
import { REPO_URL, HUB_URL } from "../config";
---

<Page
  title="What isn't true yet · Vela"
  description="An honest accounting of what Vela has not yet proven, and what would change each one."
  active="honest"
  eyebrow="Vela · operator notes"
  pageTitle="What isn't true yet"
  subtitle="An honest accounting of what Vela has not yet proven, and what would change each one."
>
  <div slot="aside">
    <a href="/" class="aside-link">← home</a>
    <span>·</span>
    <a href="/protocol" class="aside-link">protocol</a>
    <span>·</span>
    <a href={REPO_URL} class="aside-link">github</a>
  </div>

  <article class="honest">
    <p class="honest__lede">
      Most projects publish a launch page that reads as if everything in the architecture diagram
      already exists. Vela is being built in public, and the gap between the architecture and
      what is actually true on a given Tuesday is real. This page names that gap, deliberately,
      so a reader doesn't have to reverse-engineer it from the demo.
    </p>

    <!-- ── Gap 1 ── -->
    <section class="honest__gap" aria-labelledby="gap-signers">
      <header class="honest__gap-head">
        <span class="honest__gap-num">01</span>
        <h2 class="honest__gap-title" id="gap-signers">The only signers, today, are mine.</h2>
      </header>
      <div class="honest__gap-body">
        <p>
          The hub at <a class="inline-link" href={`${HUB_URL}/entries`} rel="noopener">{HUB_URL.replace(/^https?:\/\//, '')}/entries</a>
          currently lists three signed frontier entries. All three were signed by an Ed25519
          key under my control. The signature chain works, the byte-identical replay works,
          the validator works — but none of it has been exercised by a key I cannot also revoke.
        </p>
        <dl class="honest__gap-pair">
          <dt>What's true now</dt>
          <dd>
            One signer · 188 findings · 11 contradictions · the protocol's surface holds at single-actor scale.
          </dd>
          <dt>What would change it</dt>
          <dd>
            One external lab, journal, or researcher signs and publishes a frontier entry under their own key. The hub
            verifies it, the network locator resolves, and a third party can re-replay it. That single event moves Vela
            from "specification with one implementation" to "specification with adoption."
          </dd>
          <dt>What you could do</dt>
          <dd>
            <code>git clone {REPO_URL}</code>, generate a keypair with <code>vela sign generate-keypair</code>, sign a frontier
            covering whatever bounded question you actually work on, and publish it to the hub. There is no allowlist.
          </dd>
        </dl>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── Gap 2 ── -->
    <section class="honest__gap" aria-labelledby="gap-corridor">
      <header class="honest__gap-head">
        <span class="honest__gap-num">02</span>
        <h2 class="honest__gap-title" id="gap-corridor">One corridor is not the field.</h2>
      </header>
      <div class="honest__gap-body">
        <p>
          The Alzheimer's Therapeutics frontier is the only corridor running against real
          published evidence today. It has 188 findings, 11 contradictions, and one worked
          Correction event (pericyte loss → APOE4-narrowed scope). The protocol's claim is
          field-general — but until a second corridor exists, that claim is a hypothesis,
          not a result.
        </p>
        <dl class="honest__gap-pair">
          <dt>What's true now</dt>
          <dd>
            One non-trivial corridor, 86 papers ingested, three real signed events including a Correction with
            scope narrowing. The shape works for neurovascular dementia.
          </dd>
          <dt>What would change it</dt>
          <dd>
            A second corridor in a structurally different field — e.g., catalyst design, single-cell methods,
            superconductor materials, or a clinical trial registry — built on the same primitives. If the same
            Finding / Evidence / Correction / Contradiction model carries the load there, the field-general
            claim earns its keep.
          </dd>
          <dt>What you could do</dt>
          <dd>
            Pick a question your lab cannot afford to keep relearning. Ten findings is enough to start;
            the protocol is more useful at small scale than people expect.
          </dd>
        </dl>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── Gap 3 ── -->
    <section class="honest__gap" aria-labelledby="gap-production">
      <header class="honest__gap-head">
        <span class="honest__gap-num">03</span>
        <h2 class="honest__gap-title" id="gap-production">No journal, funder, or AI lab uses Vela in production.</h2>
      </header>
      <div class="honest__gap-body">
        <p>
          The infrastructure-adoption story is the one that takes years. Git existed before
          GitHub had network effects. The PDB existed before journals required deposition.
          Vela is in the period where the spec and the binary work, and the social layer that
          would make it load-bearing has not formed yet. Pretending otherwise would be
          worse than naming it.
        </p>
        <dl class="honest__gap-pair">
          <dt>What's true now</dt>
          <dd>
            Working spec · open protocol · running hub · two implementations of the verifier (Rust, Python).
            Zero institutional integrations.
          </dd>
          <dt>What would change it</dt>
          <dd>
            A journal accepts a signed Correction event as a first-class submission, instead of requiring a
            four-page paper to weaken a claim by 30%. A funder asks grantees to deposit findings into a public
            substrate as a condition of award. An AI lab agrees to write its agent-generated proposals into a
            public log so that the next generation of models can inherit them. Any one of those changes the gradient.
          </dd>
          <dt>What you could do</dt>
          <dd>
            If you edit a journal, fund science, or run an AI scientific-agents program: a 30-minute conversation
            costs me almost nothing and may be the highest-leverage thing you read this week.
            <a class="inline-link" href="mailto:will@vela.science">will@vela.science</a>.
          </dd>
        </dl>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── Closing — operator note ── -->
    <section class="honest__close">
      <p class="honest__close-line">
        The reason this page exists is that I would rather be told these gaps before
        someone funds the work than after. If you have read this far and noticed an
        honest gap that isn't on the page, that's the email I want most.
      </p>
      <p class="honest__close-meta">
        Last reviewed: 2026-05-02
        <span class="honest__sep">·</span>
        <a class="inline-link" href="/">Back to the live frontier →</a>
        <span class="honest__sep">·</span>
        <a class="inline-link" href="/protocol">Read the protocol →</a>
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Page>

<style>
  .aside-link {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--size-xs);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--ink-3);
  }
  .aside-link:hover { color: var(--gold); }
  div[slot="aside"] {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
  }

  .inline-link {
    color: var(--ink-1);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--gold) 56%, transparent);
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
    transition: color var(--dur-1) var(--ease), text-decoration-color var(--dur-1) var(--ease);
  }
  .inline-link:hover {
    color: var(--gold);
    text-decoration-color: var(--gold);
  }

  /* ── Honest page ── */
  .honest {
    max-width: var(--measure-wide, 72ch);
    padding: 8px 0 32px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .honest__lede {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.62;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--ink-1) 92%, var(--ink-2));
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-7);
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }

  .honest__gap {
    border-top: 1px solid color-mix(in oklab, var(--gold) 32%, transparent);
    padding: var(--space-5) 0 var(--space-6);
  }
  .honest__gap:last-of-type {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-2);
  }
  .honest__gap-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 14px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  .honest__gap-num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 13px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--gold) 72%, var(--ink-2));
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .honest__gap-title {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2.4vw, 1.55rem);
    line-height: 1.22;
    letter-spacing: -0.018em;
    color: var(--ink-0);
    margin: 0;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .honest__gap-body p {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    line-height: 1.62;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--ink-1) 90%, var(--ink-2));
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-4);
    max-width: 64ch;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }

  .honest__gap-pair {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 11rem 1fr;
    gap: 0.75rem var(--space-4);
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .honest__gap-pair {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 4px 0;
    }
    .honest__gap-pair dd { margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
  }
  .honest__gap-pair dt {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--ink-3) 92%, transparent);
    padding-top: 4px;
  }
  .honest__gap-pair dd {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.96rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    color: var(--ink-1);
    margin: 0;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }
  .honest__gap-pair code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.86em;
    background: var(--paper-1);
    padding: 1px 6px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-xs, 3px);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-1);
    color: var(--ink-0);
  }

  .honest__close {
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
    padding-top: var(--space-5);
    border-top: 1px solid color-mix(in oklab, var(--gold) 38%, transparent);
  }
  .honest__close-line {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1.8vw, 1.2rem);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--ink-1) 92%, var(--ink-2));
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-4);
    max-width: 60ch;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }
  .honest__close-meta {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--ink-3);
  }
  .honest__sep { margin: 0 8px; color: var(--ink-4); }
</style>
